{
  "texts": [
    "Enhancing stakeholder engagement through enjoyable participation methods",
    "In accordance with prior research, our study demonstrated that the participants perceived the chatbot interaction as more enjoyable than completing a traditional survey (Kim et al., 2019; Xiao et al., 2020b).",
    "Previous research emphasizes the significance of stakeholder involvement in design projects to achieve successful outcomes (Arnstein, 1969; Münster et al., 2017; Calderon, 2020).",
    "However, urban design and planning initiatives often struggle with low participation rates due to their professional and political nature (Brabham, 2009; Giering, 2011; Krüger et al., 2019; Dortheimer and Margalit, 2020).",
    "This creates difficulties in meaningfully engaging underrepresented communities in such projects."
  ]
}